{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id90010214-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s2733"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2733"},"text":"§ 2733.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Reemployment of annuitants under the Civil Service Retirement System and Federal Employees’ Retirement System","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id90010215-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s2733/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Authority","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary of State may waive the application of section 8344 or 8468 of title 5 on a case-by-case basis, for employment of an annuitant in a position in the Department of State for which there is exceptional difficulty in recruiting or retaining a qualified employee, or when a temporary emergency hiring need exists.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id90010216-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s2733/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Procedures","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary should prescribe procedures for the exercise of any authority under subsection (a), including criteria for any exercise of authority and procedures for a delegation of authority.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id90010217-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s2733/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Annuitants not treated as employees for purposes of retirement benefits","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"An employee for whom a waiver under this section is in effect shall not be considered an employee for purposes of subchapter III of chapter 83, or chapter 84 of title 5.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id90010218-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1956-08-01/ch841"},"text":"Aug. 1, 1956, ch. 841","children":[],"tail":", title I, § 61, as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/234/tI/s1602/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–234, title I, § 1602(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2006-06-15"},"text":"June 15, 2006","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/120/441"},"text":"120 Stat. 441","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/32/tXI/s1115/c/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–32, title XI, § 1115(c)(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2009-06-24"},"text":"June 24, 2009","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/123/1905"},"text":"123 Stat. 1905","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/323/tIV/s405/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–323, title IV, § 405(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2016-12-16"},"text":"Dec. 16, 2016","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/130/1929"},"text":"130 Stat. 1929","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id90010219-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id9001021a-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"id9001021b-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/234/tI/s1602/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–234, title I, § 1602(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2006-06-15"},"text":"June 15, 2006","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/120/441"},"text":"120 Stat. 441","children":[],"tail":", which directed that this section be added at the end of title I of the Department of State Basic Authorities Act of 1956, was executed by adding this section at the end of title I of the State Department Basic Authorities Act of 1956, to reflect the probable intent of Congress."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id9001021c-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2016—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/323"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–323","children":[],"tail":" amended subsec. (a) generally. Prior to amendment, subsec. (a) related to authority of the Secretary of State to waive application of provisions of section 8344 or 8468 of title 5 on a case-by-case basis for employment of certain annuitants to facilitate the assignment of persons to Iraq, Pakistan, and Afghanistan or to posts vacated by members of the Service assigned to Iraq, Pakistan, and Afghanistan and terminated the Secretary’s authority as of "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2010-10-01"},"text":"Oct. 1, 2010","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2009—Subsec. (a)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/32"},"tex